==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Acclivity
<hw>Ac*cliv"i*ty</hw>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Acclivities</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L.
<ets>acclivitas</ets>, fr. <ets>acclivis</ets>, <ets>acclivus</ets>,
ascending; <ets>ad</ets> + <ets>clivus</ets> a hill, slope, fr. root
<ets>kli</ets> to lean. See <er>Lean</er>.]</ety> <def>A slope or
inclination of the earth, as the side of a hill, considered as
<xex>ascending</xex>, in opposition to <xex>declivity</xex>, or
<xex>descending</xex>; an upward slope; ascent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Acclivous</ent>⟦br⟧
